Lurtz Battle Cry x 2<br />
Beyond the Height of Men    </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Strategy</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">Ok first to the Free Peoples strategy.<br />
<br />
This decks thing is to damage the minions before the skirmishes are resolved. As you can see, I have alot of directly damaging cards in the deck:<br />
Legolas GL, Blade of Gondor, Aragorns Bow, Bow of the Galadhrim, Orc Bane, ARV and PATHS.<br />
But now to the real strategy.<br />
I bid high to go first, and pull Sam out to remove the burdens. I hope I can get either Aragorn or Gandalf out, and play them for a lower twilight cost, thanks to Pippin. After that, I hope I can run directly to site 3 sanctuary, and, if I have the map out, I exert Pippin for my own site(s). I usually spare Pippin to exert for Thrors Map and to feed a Balrog/Troll/WK/Lurtz. Ands also, as mentioned, he lowers Gandalfs and Aragorns cost. If possible, I run from sanctuary to sanctuary, exert alot and heal. After that, I will probably be before the opponent, and I can take it easy and move one site per turn. Of course, if I have to, I will run.<br />
<br />
<br />
And now the shadow side.<br />
<br />
The shadow side is meant to only stop the opponent. I have lots of strong and high vitality Uruks combined with lots of Wizard Storms, which usually stops the opponent from double moving. A nice thing you can get out for 10 twilights is Lurtz+sword and a Scout. The Scout will take care of ARV, and the fierce Lurtz will wound!<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
Actually I havent tried the deck myself, but I think it could work pretty well. <br />
I hope you will review it! </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000"> </Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">DeckTech <BR> For the Players, By the Players  <BR>www.decktech.net </FONT></TD></TR></table> 
